main_text: "The charge that fruit eaters will suffer nutritional imbalances and deficiencies finds no basis in fact. Fruits eaten judiciously according to their seasons furnish us with every nutrient factor known and unknown in plenteousness. Those ancient Greeks whom we admire so much for their statuesque bodies were fruit eaters. Most ate heavily of apples dates oranges olives figs and grapes. The Greek and Roman gods are ascriptions born of reverence for fruit trees and food-bearing plants.The charge that fruit eaters are too thin is not borne out by even the simplest investigation. Personally I’ve gone down into the 120-pound range and came back to the 150-pound range with excellent muscular development on a diet almost entirely of fruits. My wife has to watch her intake of heavy-calorie fruit foods especially nuts lest she become too heavy. As previously pointed out the Greeks thrived on fruitarian diets. Pythagoras one of the giants of Grecian literature philosophy and mathematics was a fruitarian and had a whole school of followers who likewise were fruitarians."-TC Fry from the Life Science Course lesson 19: Ascertaining the Human Dietetic Character part II.enjoyed a juicy #papaya for breakfast yesterday. was going to keep it a #monomeal but I had two mangoes right after.so blessed for all this abundance.to read more of TC Frys Life Science Course go to the website terrain.wiki for the online version.#tcfry #lifescience #healthscience #nutrition #nutritionstudies #nutritionstudent #rawvegan #rawveganfood #veganfoodshare #fruitarian #fruitariansofig #veganbreakfastideas #vegano #desayunovegano #livingfood #eatplants #fruitariandiet #sugar #carbohydrates #highcarblowfat #alkalinefood #certifiedorgasmic

main_text: 💚 Many people know papaya in its ripe form but have you ever tried green papaya? This papaya is the same variety harvested a little earlier. It is highly valued in traditional Asian or Latin American cuisines and is difficult to come by in European markets.⁣⁣🍴It has a similar texture to zucchini and is just as versatile in the kitchen. Thai salad curry meals papaya ratatouille and candied papaya are just a few of the dishes that can be prepared. It has a mild flavor minimal calories and is easy to digest.⁣⁣😋 If you know any green papaya recipes share them in the comments below!⁣⁣⬆️ Link in stories to order organic green papayas.

main_text: マジで知らなければ食べていただろう植物…雑草が繁茂する時期ですのでどんな植物が？毒のモノは？と調べていたら意外と身近に毒が潜在しかも食べるタイミングによって毒が出て来る植物とか…😱💦農家さんはちゃんと分かってらっしゃるでしょうけど自分のような初心者は気をつけて頂いた方が良いかも💦今は初心者でもプロになるんでね！🫡学んだ事のアウトプットです✨他にもお花関係はかなりの『毒』を持つ種類がありましたでも、それが全て危ないワケではなく、気をつけるべきは小さい子供やペットが口に入れたりという点だったり、今回の様に『タイミング』であったりを学んでおく事で美味しく、安全に食べれるんだなという事を学びましたー♪#自然農法 #無農薬　#開墾中 #農業 #新規就農　#新規就農者 #子連れ農家#農業を盛り上げたい　 #農家　 #農園　 #石垣珊瑚　 #パパイヤ　 #フルーツパパイヤ　 #カニステル #マンゴスチン #トマト　 #ドラゴンフルーツ　 #マンゴーパパイヤ　 #ハイビスカス　 #沖縄　#スターフルーツ　 #フィンガーライム　 #アイスクリームバナナ　 #アテモヤ#natural farming #pesticide free #cultivating #new farmer #papaya

{"1": {"comment_id": "ito_en2021"  "comment_text": "マジで知らなければ食べていただろう
植物…

雑草が繁茂する時期ですので
どんな植物が？毒のモノは？
と調べていたら意外と身近に毒が潜在

しかも食べるタイミングによって
毒が出て来る植物とか…😱💦

農家さんはちゃんと分かってらっしゃるでしょうけど
自分のような初心者は
気をつけて頂いた方が良いかも💦

小さい子供やペットが口に入れたり
という点だったり、
今回の様に『タイミング』であったり
を学んでおく事で
美味しく、安全に食べれるんだな
という事を学びましたー♪

main_text: Could a parfait get any prettier than this?What better way to start your day than with this stunning papaya sticky rice parfait created by @rainbownourishments for @rubyrisepapaya 🧡💜Simple to make and filled with bold colour and flavour this is a recipe you'll want to save to make again and again.INGREDIENTS:1 ½ cup canned coconut milk½ cup glutinous black rice uncooked3 tablespoons maple syrup or coconut sugar to taste½ papaya¼ cup pomegranate arils1 cup coconut yoghurtMETHOD:1. Remove the seeds from the papaya and cut off the skin. Slice the papaya into cubes. You can also use a peeler to slice the papaya into thin strips or a melon baller to form balls out of the papaya.3. Enjoy immediately.#freshfood #healthyrecipes #healthycooking #delicious #papayaaustralia #papaya #tasty #chia #mango #delicious #brekkie #freshfruit #papayas #thefeedfeed #weekendbreakfast #goodmoodfood #tropical #aussiepapaya #yummy #healthy #ricepudding #parfait #stickyrice #coconut
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "papayaaustralia"  "comment_text": "Could a parfait get any prettier than this?

What better way to start your day than with this stunning papaya sticky rice parfait  created by @rainbownourishments for @rubyrisepapaya 🧡💜

Simple to make and filled with bold colour and flavour  this is a recipe you'll want to save to make again and again.

INGREDIENTS:
1 ½ cup canned coconut milk
½ cup glutinous black rice  uncooked
3 tablespoons maple syrup or coconut sugar  to taste
½ papaya
¼ cup pomegranate arils
1 cup coconut yoghurt

METHOD:
1. Add coconut milk and black rice to a small saucepan over high heat. Boil for 10 minutes and reduce to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the rice is tender and sticky. Add sweetener to taste.
2. Remove the seeds from the papaya and cut off the skin. Slice the papaya into cubes. You can also use a peeler to slice the papaya into thin strips or a melon baller to form balls out of the papaya.
3. Arrange the sticky rice  papaya  pomegranate and yoghurt into 2 jars as desired. Enjoy immediately.

Ingredients:
1 lb lean ground beef
3 cloves garlic  minced
1 tsp Italian seasoning

1 (14.5 oz.) jar diced tomatoes with juice
1 cup marinara sauce
3 large bell peppers  any color  sliced in half  seeds and membranes removed
nitrate-free pepperoni  thinly sliced
1/4 cup black pitted olives  sliced

Instructions:
Preheat your oven to 400 degrees f.
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add in ground meat  garlic  and cook while crumbling with a wooden spoon until no longer pink  about 6-8 minutes.
Drain excess grease.Season with Italian seasoning  sea salt and pepper  then stir in the diced tomatoes.
Continue to simmer on medium-low heat for 8-10 minutes  or until sauce thickens a bit.
Pour your marinara sauce into the bottom of the casserole dish and spread with a spatula.

𝐒𝐔𝐍 𝐓𝐀𝐍 𝐈𝐍 𝐒𝐏𝐑𝐈𝐍𝐆

6 oz reposado tequila
4 oz fresh squeezed orange juice
2 oz elderflower cordial (I used mine from @sauvieshrubs)
2 oz orgeat
1 half papaya  seeds and skin removed
3 scoops of ice

put all ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth! divide equally into glasses and top with a salted lime wedge.
